2006-10-26  Greg Broten  <gbroten@owl>

	* src/psos/PsosEventHandler.cpp, src/sparrow/SparrowEventHandler.cpp, src/video/VideoDeviceBTTV.cpp, src/video/VideoDeviceQuickCam.cpp:
	Updated to support the x86_64 bit architecture. In each of these files the compiler complained about a loss of precision when ask to cast a void * to an integer. Under the i386 a void * pointer and an integer are both represented by 32 bits, but under the x86_64 architecture, a void * pointer is 64 bits. The solution was to use a cast to long, which works for both architectures.

	* src/miro/Makefile.am, src/miro/SockConnection.cpp, src/miro/SockConnection.h, src/miro/SvcParameters.xml:
	Added the SockConnection class, analogous to the TtyConnection class, which simplifies interfacing with socket based devices.

2006-10-26  speedy  <speedy@owl>

	* config/search_player.m4: search for player 2.0

2006-10-25  Hans Utz  <hutz@owl>

	* src/miro/LogHeader.cpp, src/miro/LogHeader.h, src/miro/LogReader.cpp, src/miro/LogReader.h, src/miro/LogTypeRepository.cpp, src/miro/LogTypeRepository.h, src/miro/LogWriter.h:
	making log stream 64 bit arch save

