2006-02-09  Hans Utz  <hutz@owl>

	* src/video/VideoFilterRGBtoSeg.cpp, src/video/VideoFilterService.cpp, src/video/VideoFilterService.h, src/video/VideoFilterYUV420PtoRGB.cpp:
	silencing warning of gcc that seemed reasonable:
	adding virtual dtor
	splitting summation in RGBtoSeg, as gcc claimed the multiple ++
	opeartions within a method call argument as undefined.
	removed unused variable

	* src/miro/LogReader.cpp:
	Trying to fix the long standing log-file issue with recent TAO versions.
	The loading and playing of old log files now succeedes and also writing
	is possible.
	The written logfiles are of smaller size, than the original ones, which
	strikes me a bit odd.
	Need to verify this.
	Additionally, this conditional compile nightmare requires a lot of ACE/TAO
	versions to verify, which I do not have installed.
	So we should make sure, that it works for us by looking at log files.
	I'll add a bit more debug information, so we can easily see the number of
	events etc. stored in each log file.

	* src/miro/XmlParse.cpp:
	splitting up parsing for char, signed char and unsigned char types.
	- char is supposed to be a single literal character
	- signed char is supposed to be a number in the range [-128, 127]
	- unsigned char is supposed to be a number in the range [0, 255]

2006-02-03  Gerd Mayer  <gmayer@owl>

	* utils/qtVideo/MainForm.cpp:
	remove explicit limitation to 3 digits in image size. might give problems with never firewire device

	* src/video/Parameters.xml:
	change defaults values, so firewire device should work as befor without any changes

	* src/video/Parameters.xml, src/video/VideoDevice1394.cpp:
	apply patch from Sean Verret
	description taken from his email see below


	I made the changes to The ULM code to make the flea camera work.  Here
	is a summary of the changes you can pass on to Ulm:

	1. I added support for FORMAT1 type cameras.  This includes the
	MODE_1024x768_MONO format that we are interested in.

	2. I added support for SVGA_NONCOMPRESSED_1 video Format

	In order to accomplish the above tasks I defined two new variables
	videoFormat and videoMode in the Device1394 section of the parameters
	file.  These variables are used in VideoDevice1394 to pass the correct
	parameters to libdc.

	videoFormat is a string.  Valid entries are:
	VGA (This equates to the previous Ulm code)
	SVGA1 This adds support for the flea camera

	videoMode is an integre.  Valid entries are:
	0 - (Format0 cameras handle the previous Ulm code)
	1 - (Format1 handles 800x600 and 1024x768 cameras)

	* src/miro/CompassImpl.cpp, src/miro/InclinometerImpl.cpp, src/pioneer/TCM2Impl.cpp:
	apply patch from Ingo van Lil
	explanation copied form his email see below


	one of my former colleagues at university sent me a mail and reported
	frequent assertion failures in my TCM2 compass module. It looks like the
	errors are caused by inaccurate double/float rounding in several
	integrateData() methods: All my values are normalized by the
	Miro::Angle class, explicitly cast to float, and finally compared with
	M_PI. This comparison performs an implicit cast back to double, and it
	looks like these casts can make the value leave the allowed range.

	Fixing the problem is quite simple: Explicitly casting the double
	constants to float before comparing should avoid any implicit casts.
	A Patch for the CVS version is attached.

2006-01-19  Gerd Mayer  <gmayer@owl>

	* src/video/VideoConsumer.cpp:
	let the video server die in case there are no buffers for writing available.
	doesn't make any difference in functionality, but it's handy for scripting

