2005-09-29  Gerd Mayer  <gmayer@owl>

	* config/Make-rules, config/conditionals.m4, configure.ac, miro-config.in:
	now a script is made during bootstrap/configure which can be used by derived projects to determine how miro is built (try for example $MIRO_ROOT/miro-config --version).

	for convenience, the script can also be used to check for ace/tao and qt stuff. there is no need to search them again and again (not very standard-like, but useful as long as all these projects use there own, weird build system).

	additional clean up in some files

	* bin/.cvsignore, .cvsignore: add a couple of ignore files
	 CVS: ----------------------------------------------------------------------

	* src/miro/Makefile.am:
	remove BuiltIn.h entry. Otherwise it will be removed after a make clean

