	cleanup in the directory
	adding base functionality for inclusion of MCL to Miro/botsvcs
	- using <iosfwd> instead of <iostream> to cut down header inclusion
	  (need to test with old compiler versions...)
	- cleaning up and documenting TimeSeries class
	- adding now log filters: MCL and BAP
	  (need to thing about a design that omits the need for changing log.h
	  on such occasions...)
	- splitting Angle.h into header and inline file
	- adding a random number lookup table class
	- adding a header file of wrapper macros for builtin functions of gcc
	  which tend to change with different compiler versions

2005-09-08  Guillem Pages  <guillem@owl>

	* src/fusedRangeSensor/FusedRangeSensorImpl.cpp:
	Oops, forgot that one cannot initialize deleted variables :-p
	There is no point anyway if they are unused.

2005-09-06  Guillem Pages  <guillem@owl>

	* tests/fusedRangeSensor/FusedRangeSensorTest.cpp, src/fusedRangeSensor/FusedRangeSensorImpl.cpp, src/fusedRangeSensor/FusedRangeSensorImpl.h, idl/FusedRangeSensor.idl:
	Added AVERAGE fusion method.
	  It doesn't make much sense to fuse sensors that way, but you never know...
	Reimplemented the fusion itself, to solve a bug in the linear interpolation.
	  Once a sensor bunch came, it was interpolated, and the next one had to
	   compete with the interpolated values. In case of the back 180 of the laser,
	   it prevented the sonar to get meaningful values.

