2005-03-23  Gerd Mayer  <gmayer@owl>

	* configure.ac:
	I've found this %$"%% bug after 4 *Q$%$ hours of searching. uncommented the "$!"* search for @!"$% ace features again

	* tests/sphinx/Makefile.am, tests/video/Makefile.am, tests/videoBroker/Makefile.am, tests/xml/Makefile.am, utils/Joystick/Makefile.am, utils/configEditor/Makefile.am, utils/logPlayer/Makefile.am, utils/makeConfig/Makefile.am, utils/notify/Makefile.am, utils/notifyObserver/Makefile.am, utils/nsIOR/Makefile.am, utils/policyController/Makefile.am, utils/policyEditor/Makefile.am, utils/qtJoystick/Makefile.am, utils/qtTouchPad/Makefile.am, utils/qtVideo/Makefile.am, utils/rangeSensor/Makefile.am, utils/sparrowBoard/Makefile.am, utils/widgets/Makefile.am, .cvsignore, Makefile.am, all.h.sh, config/conditionals.m4, config/search_ace.m4, config/search_tao.m4, configure.ac, examples/b21Motion/Makefile.am, examples/battery/Makefile.am, examples/buttons/Makefile.am, examples/infrared/Makefile.am, examples/motion/Makefile.am, examples/notify/Makefile.am, examples/odometry/Makefile.am, examples/params/Makefile.am, examples/rangeSensor/Makefile.am, examples/robotikI/Makefile.am, examples/sonar/Makefile.am, examples/speechSimple/Makefile.am, examples/stall/Makefile.am, examples/video/Makefile.am, examples/videoFilter/Makefile.am, idl/Makefile.am, idl/ObjectVector.idl, pch/.cvsignore, pch/Makefile.am, pch/foo.cc, performance-tests/can/Makefile.am, performance-tests/faul/Makefile.am, performance-tests/logging/Makefile.am, performance-tests/mcp/Makefile.am, performance-tests/panTilt/Makefile.am, performance-tests/response/Makefile.am, performance-tests/video/Makefile.am, src/abus/Makefile.am, src/b21Base/Makefile.am, src/base/Makefile.am, src/buttons/Makefile.am, src/can/Makefile.am, src/faulMotor/Makefile.am, src/faulTty/Makefile.am, src/laser/Makefile.am, src/makeParams/Makefile.am, src/mcp/Makefile.am, src/miro/.cvsignore, src/miro/Client.h, src/miro/Makefile.am, src/miro/Server.h, src/msp/Makefile.am, src/panTilt/Makefile.am, src/params/Makefile.am, src/pioneer/Makefile.am, src/pioneerBase/Makefile.am, src/playerBase/Makefile.am, src/psos/Makefile.am, src/sparrow/Makefile.am, src/sparrowBase/Makefile.am, src/speech/Makefile.am, src/sphinx/Makefile.am, src/video/.cvsignore, src/video/Makefile.am, templates/Makefile.am.bin, templates/Makefile.am.lib.a, templates/Makefile.am.lib.so, templates/Makefile.am.qt, tests/b21/Makefile.am, tests/dpPanTilt/Makefile.am, tests/dtlk/Makefile.am, tests/faul/Makefile.am, tests/gripper/Makefile.am, tests/kicker/Makefile.am, tests/log/Makefile.am, tests/motion/Makefile.am, tests/notify/Makefile.am, tests/notifyMulticast/Makefile.am, tests/odometry/Makefile.am, tests/panTilt/Makefile.am, tests/pioneer/Makefile.am, tests/rangeSensor/Makefile.am, tests/sparrow/Makefile.am, tests/speech/Makefile.am:
	Okay, here we go. Maybe I can hit the 100-commit-mails-in-one-single-day barrier.

	- Fix for newer ACE/TAO versions. Therefore have to restructure the m4-files
	- Small fix in ObjectVector.idl (naming conflict)
	- Most notably, added support for precompiled-headers when using gcc > 3.4
	  - This needs for sure a bootstrap and configure run.
	  - The first time the configure-script runs, it may take some time, because
	    all include files are processed, precompiled, grepped, awk'ed and whatever
	    to build one single header file from ACE/TAO and Qt includes.
	  - In all subsequent configures, this step is skipped. It can be however
	    started manually by doing a "make clean" in the pch subdir or by calling the
	    script all.h.sh in $MIRO_ROOT
	  - the new subdir pch just includes this overall-header and a small dummy-programm,
	    that is used to track the dependencies (just to fool autoconf/make)
	  - btw. it is enabled with: configure --enable-PCH


	I someone encounter problems with this, please report it to me...

