	* src/playerBase/PlayerMotionImpl.cpp, src/playerBase/PlayerReactorTask.cpp:
	It is not a good idea to specify a speed in mm/s when the server expects m/s
	It is also a bad idea to assign a variable befor the constructor is even called
	Got ridden of those bad ideas.
	Also implemented the simulated battery. Useful? No. Nice? Yep. Why then? Because.

