2005-01-14  Gerd Mayer  <gmayer@owl>

	* etc/SparrowDefault.xml, etc/barney.xml, etc/coyote.xml, etc/flying-eagle.xml, etc/gonzales.xml, etc/roadrunner.xml, etc/rosita.xml, etc/speedy.xml:
	adopt config file to new camera/device format

	* src/miro/Parameters.xml, src/video/BufferManager.cpp, src/video/BufferManager.h, src/video/BufferManager1394.cpp, src/video/BufferManagerBTTV.cpp, src/video/BufferManagerMeteor.cpp, src/video/BufferManagerQuickCam.cpp, src/video/Parameters.xml:
	CameraParameters are now part of the device definition and can therefore be applied to each device seperatly.

	old way (example):

	      <parameter name="Miro::CameraParameters" >
	        <parameter value="0.060000" name="Latency" />
	        <parameter value="34.0" name="Alpha" />
	        <parameter value="595" name="Height" />
	        <parameter value=" 6.4000000000e+02" name="Ncx" />
	        <parameter value=" 6.4000000000e+02" name="Nfx" />
	        <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dx" />
	        <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dy" />
	        <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dpx" />
	        <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dpy" />
	      </parameter>

	      <instance type="Video::Device1394Parameters" name="Device1394" >
	        <parameter value="-1" name="Focus" />
	        <parameter value="128" name="Hue" />
	      </instance>

	new way:

	      <instance type="Video::Device1394Parameters" name="Device1394" >
		<parameter value="-1" name="Focus" />
		<parameter value="128" name="Hue" />

		<parameter name="Camera" >
		  <parameter value="0.060000" name="Latency" />
		  <parameter value="34.0" name="Alpha" />
		  <parameter value="595" name="Height" />
		  <parameter value=" 6.4000000000e+02" name="Ncx" />
		  <parameter value=" 6.4000000000e+02" name="Nfx" />
		  <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dx" />
		  <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dy" />
		  <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dpx" />
		  <parameter value=" 7.4000000000e-03" name="Dpy" />
		</parameter>
	      </instance>

	* config/search_tao.m4: damn, second version

	* config/search_tao.m4:
	add another path to linker call for future tao version

2005-01-10  Hans Utz  <hutz@owl>

	* src/video/VideoDeviceMeteor.cpp: fixing bug on MIRO_DBG macro

	* src/video/DeviceAsynchLinkManager.cpp:
	removing conditional copilation

	* src/video/.cvsignore, src/video/AsynchBufferSet.cpp, src/video/AsynchBufferSet.h, src/video/AsynchLinkManager.cpp, src/video/AsynchLinkManager.h, src/video/AsynchPreLink.cpp, src/video/AsynchPreLink.h, src/video/AsynchSuccLink.cpp, src/video/AsynchSuccLink.h, src/video/BufferManager.cpp, src/video/BufferManager.h, src/video/DeviceAsynchBufferSet.cpp, src/video/DeviceAsynchBufferSet.h, src/video/DeviceAsynchLinkManager.cpp, src/video/DeviceAsynchLinkManager.h, src/video/Makefile.am, src/video/Parameters.xml, src/video/VideoBrokerImpl.cpp, src/video/VideoConsumer.cpp, src/video/VideoDevice.cpp, src/video/VideoDevice.h, src/video/VideoDeviceDummy.cpp, src/video/VideoFilter.cpp, src/video/VideoFilter.h, src/video/VideoFilter.i, src/video/VideoFilterLink.h, src/video/VideoFilterRGBtoSeg.cpp, src/video/VideoServer.cpp, src/video/VideoServer.h:
	extending the VIP framework to asynchronous video processing
	now multiple filter trees can be interlinked and are synchronized as needed
	at least in theroy :-)
	in theory it should also be completely unintrusive for synchronous trees
	any deviations from theory can be proven wrong and therefore do not exist
	- or get fixed ASAP

	* examples/videoFilter/AsynchVideoConfig.xml, examples/videoFilter/BusyVideoConfig.xml, examples/videoFilter/DiffVideoConfig.xml, examples/videoFilter/FilterBusy.cpp, examples/videoFilter/FilterBusy.h, examples/videoFilter/FilterDiff.cpp, examples/videoFilter/GrayVideoService.cpp, examples/videoFilter/Makefile.am, examples/videoFilter/MultiAsynchLinksConfig.xml, examples/videoFilter/Parameters.xml:
