	- switching all servers to use the new config parameter names
	  also using the configuration class to get over with it
	- adding parameter entries for every filter, to make them visible in
	  the config editor, adding the entries to the Filter implementations, too
	- removing the Video::Parameters singleton
	  now we create a video device instance for every Video::Parameters instance
	  in the config file. stereo vision processing here we come

	* src/miro/ConfigDocument.cpp, src/miro/ConfigDocument.h, src/miro/Configuration.cpp, src/miro/Configuration.h, src/miro/Makefile.am, src/miro/NotifyMulticastAdapter.cpp:
	splitting up config file handling
	the Configuration class does hold a static init method
	that performs command line parameter parsing for MiroConfigFile
	it also holds a singleton pointing to the miro config document
	(if initialized by init() otherwise its an empty document)

	added a default constructor to ConfigDocument, so we can use it in a singleton
	added init/fini methods for deferred initialization of the class
	added checks to skip parameter processing on an uninitialized class

