2004-08-25  Gonzales  <gonzales@owl>

	* src/miro/LogReader.cpp, src/miro/LogWriter.cpp:
	some cleanup on Any-parsing backward compability code after
	testing it with an apropriate TAO version

2004-08-25  Hans Utz  <hutz@owl>

	* src/miro/LogReader.cpp, src/miro/LogWriter.cpp:
	adding backward compability code for log file parsing with older TAO version

2004-08-24  Hans Utz  <hutz@owl>

	* utils/logPlayer/FileSet.cpp, utils/logPlayer/FileSet.h, utils/logPlayer/LogFile.cpp, utils/logPlayer/LogFile.h, utils/logPlayer/MainForm.cpp, utils/logPlayer/MainForm.h, utils/logPlayer/Makefile.am:
	using the new logging infrastructure

	* src/miro/LogTypeRepository.cpp, src/miro/LogTypeRepository.h:
	missed these two files on the last commit, sorry

	* src/miro/Exception.cpp, src/miro/Exception.h, src/miro/LogHeader.cpp, src/miro/LogHeader.h, src/miro/LogNotifyConsumer.cpp, src/miro/LogNotifyConsumer.h, src/miro/LogReader.cpp, src/miro/LogReader.h, src/miro/LogWriter.cpp, src/miro/LogWriter.h, src/miro/Makefile.am, src/miro/SvcParameters.xml:
	committing the new and improved event logging infrastructure
	a new log file format:
	log file header (8 Byte) (defined in LogHeader.h)
	- id (long = MLOG)
	- byte order (ushort)
	- version (ushort = 2)
	type code repository (defined in LogTypeRepository.h)
	- num entries (long = n)
	- type codes (n)
	-> type codes get written now only once
	cdr stream with log records
	- TimeT time stamp (ulonglong)
	- event size (ulong)
	  -> can be used to skip parsing the event body on log file loading
	  -> 0 indicates the last event in the stream
	- structured event cdr
	 * header
	 * filterable_data
	 * type code id from repository (above)
	 * the data of the any

	The LogWrite implements writing of these log files and is used
	by LogNotifyConsumer. LogReader can parse both, old and new log file format
	and is used be the LogPlayer.
	Performance of the logging framework is identical for writing log files,
	and sending logs by the log player. Initial parsing of log files is mutch
	improved for the LogPlayer. Converting log files needs a bit too much
	memory. Maybe we should improve on that one. - An equivalent tool to
	LogTruncate is currently missing for logfiles saved i.e. on NixPlayer crash.

	Did some cleanup on Exception.h/cpp to improve ostream output for exceptions.
	operator << now calls virtual Exception::printToStream. instead of doing the
	all the work himself. So only one operator << is needed and all Miro::Exception
	based exceptions can be ostreamed by a catch on Miro::Exception. If an
	exception wants to output additional data, it just has to overwrite
	printToStream

2004-08-17  Hans Utz  <hutz@owl>

	* utils/logPlayer/LogFile.cpp, utils/logPlayer/LogPlayer.cpp:
	the usual std:: stuffwq

	* utils/logPlayer/ChannelManager.cpp, utils/logPlayer/FileSet.cpp, utils/logPlayer/FileSet.h, utils/logPlayer/LogFile.cpp, utils/logPlayer/LogFile.h, utils/logPlayer/LogPlayer.cpp, utils/logPlayer/MainForm.cpp:
	fixing up multi file support that was broken by the last set of features
	- multiple files can be specified at the command line
	- the start/end times are calculated correctly if a file is added
	- tuning parsing process in terms of memory usage (helps also parsing speed)
	  on file open: the tree of available domain names/type names is represented
	  directly as char const * instead of QString. So we do not need to
	  allocate a new char array for comparing char * with QString but use strcmp.
	  As these are all readonly strings its not too ugly a hack. - Unluckily TAO
	  copies the string from the CDR stream in the first place, so a zero copy
	  implementation would need handcrafted parsing methods...
	adding multiple robots within one logfile support for replay
	- each file can now support multiple event channels
	- also multiple domain names (mandatory for the last item)
	improving performance for large file set replay by implementing
	replay synchronisation via heapifying (also this is a rather theoretical
	impovement for less than 32 files...) in order to learn a bit more about
	algorithms provided by stl

