ries.h, src/miro/TtyConnection.cpp, src/miro/VideoHelper.cpp, src/msp/Parameters.xml, src/panTilt/Parameters.xml, src/psos/Parameters.xml, src/video/BufferManager.cpp, src/video/BufferManager.h, src/video/VideoDeviceBTTV.cpp, src/video/VideoFilter.h, tests/b21/Makefile.am, tests/dpPanTilt/Makefile.am, tests/dtlk/Makefile.am, tests/faul/Makefile.am, tests/gripper/Makefile.am, tests/log/Makefile.am, tests/motion/Makefile.am, tests/notify/Makefile.am, tests/notify/NotifyTest.cpp, tests/odometry/Makefile.am, tests/panTilt/Makefile.am, tests/pioneer/Makefile.am, tests/rangeSensor/Makefile.am, tests/sparrow/Makefile.am, tests/speech/Makefile.am, tests/sphinx/Makefile.am, tests/video/Makefile.am, tests/videoBroker/Makefile.am, tests/xml/Makefile.am, utils/Joystick/Makefile.am, utils/Makefile.am, utils/logPlayer/LogFile.h, utils/logPlayer/Makefile.am, utils/makeConfig/Makefile.am, utils/notify/Makefile.am, utils/notify/NotifyLogPlayer.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/Makefile.am, utils/nsIOR/Makefile.am:
	okay, this will touch most directories of Miro
	I just write one message for all of it
	I compiled everything after a make disclean -
	so I'm quite positive, that  everything still works
	anyhow, brace for impact

	Documenting Log.h making it hopfully more usable for other developers

	Trying to properly separate miroSvc.a from miro.so
	-> It should be possible to link to miro.so without linking miroSvc.a
	Linking miro.so with miroIDL.so as it is needed anyways.
	-> It should be possible to link to miro.so without linking miroIDL.so
	Propagating this change through the sources

	Splitting up Parameters.xml into Parameters.xml and SvcParameters.xml.
	This way we can skip some classes from inclusion into miro.so
	Additionally we may need to recompile less on changes in
	SvcParameters.xml
	Propagating this change through the souces

	Adding and removing headers for compability with ACE 5.4/TAO 1.4
	We need to make sure Miro compiles with the current stable release of
	ACE/TAO. - There is a vired bug in ACE 5.3/TAO 1.4/g++ 3.3.1 witch
	requires to include cmath before OS.h. So this workaround was
	propagated through the sources, too.

	added a chapter from Gerd about autoconf and automake to the manual
	appendix - moved the part from the writing_a_client.tex about
	Makefiles to this chapter, too.

	silencing cvs by adding even more .cvsignore entries. It's fascitating
	how mutch you can ignore while building miro...

	removed PositionTracker.h form src/miro as it is actullay substituted
	by OdometryTracking, which in turn needs to be unified with the
	version residing in the Nix repository.

	* utils/logPlayer/ChannelManager.cpp, utils/Makefile.am:
	adding the notifyObserver to the make process
	registering the eventchannel factory in the naming service
	for inspection by the NotifyObserver tool

	* configure.ac: adding the notifyObserver to the configuration
	readded the makeConfig utility to the configuration

	* utils/makeConfig/.cvsignore: added another ignore entry

	* utils/notifyObserver/.cvsignore, utils/notifyObserver/ApplicationWindow.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/ApplicationWindow.h, utils/notifyObserver/ConsumerAdmin.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/ConsumerAdmin.h, utils/notifyObserver/EventChannel.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/EventChannel.h, utils/notifyObserver/EventChannelFactory.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/EventChannelFactory.h, utils/notifyObserver/EventTypeDialog.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/EventTypeDialog.h, utils/notifyObserver/FilterAdmin.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/FilterAdmin.h, utils/notifyObserver/Makefile.am, utils/notifyObserver/NotifyObserver.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/NotifyPublish.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/NotifyPublish.h, utils/notifyObserver/NotifySubscribe.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/NotifySubscribe.h, utils/notifyObserver/ProxyConsumer.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/ProxyConsumer.h, utils/notifyObserver/ProxySupplier.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/ProxySupplier.h, utils/notifyObserver/QoSAdmin.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/QoSAdmin.h, utils/notifyObserver/SupplierAdmin.cpp, utils/notifyObserver/SupplierAdmin.h:
	adding a utility for examining the NotificationService
	it is not entirely usefull yet, but helps in understanding the
	notification service a lot - at least I think so.
	Start a Notify_Service (or a LogPlayer or any server) and launch the
	NofityObserver afterwards. It will show you all the channels, consumers
	and suppliers - as well as the offered and subscribed messages

	* utils/widgets/Item.cpp, utils/widgets/Item.h, utils/widgets/Makefile.am:
	added a helper class for QListViewItems
	its used by the upcoming utility NotifyObserver

